title: BWI hosts record number of passengers in FY2015
text:
BWI hosts record number of passengers in FY2015 BWI sets passenger record in 2015 fiscal year Barbara Haddock Taylor / Baltimore Sun 
Linthicum, MD -- A scene at BWI Thurgood Marshall International Airport's Southwest Terminal. The airport handled a record of more than 22.7 million passengers in the fiscal year ended June 30. 
Linthicum, MD -- A scene at BWI Thurgood Marshall International Airport's Southwest Terminal. The airport handled a record of more than 22.7 million passengers in the fiscal year ended June 30. (Barbara Haddock Taylor / Baltimore Sun) BWI Thurgood Marshall Airport BWI hosts record number of passengers in FY2015, beating 2012 
The number of passengers at Baltimore Washington International Thurgood Marshall Airport flew to new heights in the 12 months that ended in June, with more than 22.7 million passengers over the fiscal year, officials said Tuesday.
